San Diego, California  Sunday   January 29, 1911      Lt. Theodore G. Ellyson   First flight

****  &quot; the flight was short but successful, and is the first ever made by a Naval officer&quot;
( New York Times January 30, 1911)

****&quot;..the flight was witnessed by a large crowd at the Coronado Country Club&quot;  ( New York Tribune January 30, 1911)

*** &quot;.. witnessed by 10,000 persons on the polo field of the Country Club of Coronado&quot;
&quot; Ellyson rose to a height of 15 feet... but only covered about 200 yards.&quot;   &quot; .. speed estimated at 35 Miles per hour,..&quot; ( San Francisco Call January 30, 1911)
